==Japanese==
[[Image:Japanese Katakana E.png|thumb|right|Katakana character エ]]
===Etymology===
Simplified in the [[w:Heian period|Heian period]] from the ''[[man'yōgana]]'' ([[万葉仮名]]) kanji [[江]] (''e''), taken from the right part of the character.

===Stroke order===
[[Image:Japanese Katakana E Stroke.png]]

===Katakana character===
'''エ''' (''e'')

# the [e] phoneme, typically in words of non-Japanese origins
#: The fourth character of the first column of the [[katakana]] [[syllabary]], it is analogous to [[え]] (''e'') in the [[hiragana]] syllabary. The previous katakana character is [[ウ]] (''u'') and the next is [[オ]] (''o'').

